value.title: John McCain's widow says it's time for Trump to 'accept the results and get on with the healing'
value.excerpt: Cindy McCain described Joe Biden as "a man of honor" who would "heal the wounds caused by the outgoing administration."

value.title: Pope Francis congratulates Biden on election win during phone conversation
value.excerpt: Joe Biden and Pope Francis held a phone conversation on Thursday, as the pontiff became the latest world leader to congratulate the president-elect.

value.title: 'Brown girl, brown girl' poem celebrates Kamala Harris making history as 1st woman of color vice president
value.excerpt: Honoré was in the car with her 20-year-old daughter and as they celebrated the victory that will make Harris the first woman and woman of color vice president, Honoré also began to pen an update to a poem she originally wrote in 2016 for her book of poetry,

value.title: Trump has tried to coopt the Army. This new museum shows why that won’t be easy.
value.excerpt: Smart, clear and a little institutional, the museum at Fort Belvoir is a major addition to the cultural landscape.

value.title: Donald Trump lost the presidency. Residents and realtors of Trump Tower think it may become valuable again.
value.excerpt: "I'm hoping that if he doesn't come back there, and we take his name off the building, we could have a wonderful spot to live again," said one owner.

value.title: Rubio on Trump’s election lawsuits: Let the system work, don’t know what the ‘freak-out’ is about
value.excerpt: Sen. Marco Rubio, R-Fla., slammed Democrats for going after President Trump's election lawsuits after Joe Biden was projected to be the president-elect Saturday.

value.title: Chicago mayor hails 'new day for science' in playful video swiping at Trump's coronavirus response
value.excerpt: Chicago Mayor Lori Lightfoot hailed a "new day for science" in the wake of President-elect Joe Biden's announcement of a new coronavirus task force, recording a mocking video to take a swipe at President Donald Trump, who has downplayed the virus and frequently disregarded his own health officials.

value.title: Schumer blasts GOP senators for throwing 'temper tantrum' over election results: 'President Trump lost'
value.excerpt: Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer took aim at his Republican colleagues on Thursday, accusing them of "spreading conspiracy theories" about last week's election.

value.title: 'Trump vaccine'-trashing Cuomo snubbed Azar, skipped 17 White House meetings
value.excerpt: New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo has skipped more than a dozen White House meetings.

value.title: How long can Republicans keep helping Trump delegitimize the election?
value.excerpt: There are some cracks starting to show – but strong political reasons for Republicans to hang on until Georgia Senate runoffs in January

value.title: Pelosi says Republicans are "refusing to accept reality" of Biden victory
value.excerpt: Speaker Nancy Pelosi and Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer condemned Republicans for not acting on coronavirus.

value.title: Obama says Trump used his 'birther' lie to give millions of white Americans 'spooked' by a Black president an 'elixir for their racial anxiety'
value.excerpt: "For millions of Americans spooked by a Black man in the White House, he promised an elixir for their racial anxiety," Obama writes of Trump.

value.title: Trump 'letting litigation play out' in key election states, PA voters allege 'unequal system': McEnany
value.excerpt: Trump campaign senior adviser Kayleigh McEnany previewed "a number of affidavits" to be filed in Pennsylvania Thursday alleging an "unequal system."

value.title: 'Elders' group of ex-leaders founded by Mandela urges Trump to accept defeat
value.excerpt: The Elders, a group of prominent former world leaders, voiced concern on Thursday at U.S. President Donald Trump's refusal to concede electoral defeat, saying it showed disrespect for the integrity of American democracy.

value.title: A Biden COVID-19 advisor called for a national lockdown lasting up to 6 weeks. The US had a 'big pool of money' to pay for any lost wages, he said.
value.excerpt: Dr. Michael Osterholm said the US had a "big pool of money" that could get the economy back on track during lockdown while a vaccine rolls out.

value.title: Mississippi lawmaker apologizes after calling for state to leave US over Biden win
value.excerpt: The prospect of a Joe Biden presidency was a deal breaker, one Republican state lawmaker in Mississippi appeared to say last week.

value.title: GOP senator says he’ll ‘step in’ if Biden doesn’t receive intel briefings by Friday
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden should be able to receive intelligence briefings by Friday, a Republican member of the U.S. Senate said in a radio interview that aired Wednesday.

value.title: Biden chooses longtime adviser Ron Klain as chief of staff
value.excerpt: WASHINGTON -- President-elect Joe Biden has chosen his longtime adviser Ron Klain to reprise his role as his chief of staff, installing an aide with decades of experience in the top role in his White House.

value.title: Election 2020 live updates: Bolton says Republicans 'coddling' Trump; Georgia will do hand recount
value.excerpt: Both Trump and Biden took part in Veterans Day ceremonies Wednesday. Biden continues the transition process as Trump contests the election.

value.title: Donald Trump supporters can get free food at Kentucky restaurants owned by the same couple. But there's a catch.
value.excerpt: Louisville restaurant owners Troy King and Selena Johnson are offering free food to anyone who trades in Donald Trump merchandise.

value.title: FLASHBACK: Biden's chief of staff pick admits Obama admin did everything wrong with H1N1
value.excerpt: The former Obama administration official said it was pure luck H1N1 wasn’t one of the great mass casualty events in American history.

value.title: Trump officials mocked Democrats in 2016 as 'sore losers' for not accepting election results
value.excerpt: Top Donald Trump campaign and White House officials continue to baselessly assert there was widespread election fraud in the 2020 election and refuse to acknowledge President-elect Joe Biden's victory, but four years ago, those close to Trump mocked Democrats who didn't accept his victory as "sore losers."

value.title: Biden names Ron Klain as his White House chief of staff
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is poised to name his White House chief of staff as early as Thursday, with longtime adviser Ron Klain the leading finalist for the post, three people familiar with the matter tell CNN.

value.title: McMaster warns Biden on Iran deal: Don't resurrect 'political disaster masquerading as diplomatic triumph'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden should not rejoin the 2015 Iran nuclear deal once he takes office, former National Security Adviser Gen. H.R. McMaster told "Special Report" Wednesday.

value.title: Trump endorses Ronna McDaniel to remain RNC chair
value.excerpt: U.S. President Donald Trump on Wednesday endorsed Republican National Commmittee chair Ronna McDaniel to stay on in her position, crediting her with much of the support Trump received in the presidential election that he lost but is contesting.
